default2. The main
default issues
default&#xa0;
defaultAffordable housing and shortfalls in housing-related benefitsdefault&#xa0;
default2.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCitizens Advice endorses
default the definition of “affordable housing” adopted by Lord Whitty’s independent inquiry into affordable homes
default:
default “comfortable, secure homes in sound condition that are available to rent or buy without leaving households unable to afford their other basic needs
default (eg food, clothing, heating, transport and social life)”. 
default&#xa0;
default2.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs regards rents eligible for HB - and in due course the rental element of UC - we fully accept that HB/ UC cannot be expected to meet any rent, however high. But limits must take account of the 
defaultconse
defaultquences for poverty and social exclusion
default and our bureaux are picking up growing numbers of cases where HB cuts are causing hardship 
defaultand debt
default.
default 
defaultThe role of such limits in leaving claimants with inadequate disposable incomes after paying the rent is ther
defaultefore part of a wider problem – pointing to the need to develop a strategy for genuinely affordable housing in all sectors.
default&#xa0;
default2.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDisc
defaultretionary Housing Payments (
defaultDHPs
default) have featured prominently in the current debate as a possible solution to HB cuts in individu
defaultal cases
default and CAB advice on DHPs has almost trebled in the first quarter of 2013-14 compared with the same quarter the previous year
default.
default However, their 
defaultpotential 
defaultrole is exaggerated
default, given the scale of the problem
default. A perspective can be gained from the fact tha
defaultt in the current year (2013-14) the overall DHP b
defaultudget is equivalent to about seven
default per cent of the HB cuts total
default. The consequent tight
default rationing means that payments, even when made, are frequently temporary
default, with no guaran
defaulttee that the claimant will be
default able to find 
defaultsomewhere affordable 
defaultby the time the DHP expires.
default&#xa0;
defaultShared accommodation ratedefault (SAR)default&#xa0;
default2.4
