defaultm
defaultmodation,
default whether they do or not. Previously, it applied to single childless under-25s, but from January 2012 was extended to single childless under-35s. (It also applies to older people who actually do live in shared accommodation).
default 
defaultThe SAR causes major 
defaultproblems of affordability of adequate accommodation.
default Sharing is often not appropriate (see case illustration below) or accommodation within the SAR
default is simply unavailable.
