default&#xa0;
default2.24
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is important to note also that a policy of normally 
defaultmandatory direct payment to tenants
default 
defaultmilitates against principles of choice.
default&#xa0;
default2.25
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUnless there is a reason for mandatory direct payment to the 
defaultlandlord (rent arrears above a specified level or vulnerability issues such as drug or alcohol abuse) the choice, in our view, should lie with the claimant as to who – claimant or landlord – should receive benefit payments for rent. This could be on an “op
defaultt in” basis (analogous to setting up a direct debit) to satisfy the Government’s concern with active claimant engagement. 
default&#xa0;
default2.26
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAt the very least, this option should be available for a transitional period of no less than a year, to enable any necessary money a
defaultdvice and financial capability support to be put in place.
default&#xa0;
defaultA CAB in 
defaultWales
default advised a 50-year-old single woman living in a housing association property. She rec
defaulteived
default ESA
default,
default had fibromyalgia and was
default also ver
defaulty forgetful. Her HB was originally
