default&#xa0;
default2.28
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn our view, both central and local government should therefore have in place an adequate 
defaultsupport strategy for claimants in need of money advice (including benefits, debt and financia
defaultl capability). This should include input from
default our
default bureaux, with appropriate funding.
default For our part, as well as providing support to individuals, we will be able to share our findings from our Managing Migration project to help develop innovative approaches 
defaultto helping claimants with the transition to the new system.
default&#xa0;
default3. Conclusions
default&#xa0;
default3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe impact of these changes are being felt by our clients across every area of 
defaultEngland
default and 
defaultWales
default. Over time, given the range of benefit changes and against the backdrop of higher 
defaultcosts of living in general, many people both in and out of work will face increasing challenges to pay their rent or mortgage.
default&#xa0;
default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhile the drive to reduce rising housing costs within benefit spending totals is understandable, this will not be effectively ac
defaulthieved by simply cutting benefits. It’s now vital that we see the development of policies aimed at driving down housing costs themselves. Without this more strategic approach, blunt policies to cut entitlement will have a serious impact on family finances 
defaultin the short and the longer term, with all the attendant consequences for poverty, social inclusion, health and wellbeing.
default&#xa0;
default3.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs regards the roll-out of UC, we have noted in the previous section
default that our research suggests a substantial need
default for support among
default people who would otherwise struggle with the new payment systems. 
defaultIt is also 
defaultcrucial to remember the additional challenges for budgeting that people will face, not just as a result of the changes to how support is paid, but because of the greater risks of
default income shortfalls, sudden or otherwise. It is one thing to adjust to a monthly budget, but when managing a rent shortfall over a long period or a sudden income cut due to, say, the loss of 
defaultESA
default and/ o
defaultr of DLA
default, or perhaps incurring a benefit sanction, 
defaultsevere debt may suddenly no longer be avoidable.
default&#xa0;
